// Type-checks the TEST sources — which NOTHING else does.
//
// Why this file exists: `tsconfig.json` includes `src/**/*.ts` and then
// EXPLICITLY excludes `src/**/*.test.ts`, while the whole `test/` tree sits
// outside `include` altogether. Vitest transpiles per-file via esbuild and does
// not type-check at all. So before this config, all 56 test files were gated by
// NEITHER — a type-level test could pass green while the type it asserted did
// not exist (proven at RED). A fixed enumeration (`src/**`) cannot gate an
// open-ended property (any file), so the fix is a config whose include IS the
// test tree, plus a CI step that runs it (see .github/workflows/parity.yml).
//
// This is check-only: `noEmit` (so `composite`/`declaration` from the base are
// turned off — they require emit), and `rootDir` widens to the package root
// because the test tree lives beside `src`, not under it.
//
// The JSX/type settings mirror tsconfig.tui.json because several suites import
// `../src/tui.js` (→ src/tui.tsx). The base config's `exclude` does NOT keep
// tui.tsx out here: `exclude` only filters `include` globbing, it never blocks
// a file reached through an import — so tui.tsx gets pulled in and needs its
// JSX pragma and ambient types available.
{
  "extends": "./tsconfig.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "composite": false,
    "declaration": false,
    "noEmit": true,
    "rootDir": ".",
    "jsx": "react-jsx",
    "jsxImportSource": "@opentui/react",
    "types": ["node", "react", "bun"]
  },
  "include": ["test/**/*.ts", "src/**/*.test.ts"],
  "exclude": []
}
